# Frontend config. Copy to `frontend/.env.local` (gitignored) for local dev.
#
# WHAT THIS CHANGES
#
#   Unset:
#     The page renders from the committed public/results.json only. No backend,
#     no Run button.
#
#   Set:
#     The page still renders the snapshot instantly, then upgrades to live data
#     from the backend in the background, and the "Run pipeline" button appears.
#     The banner at the top tells you which mode you actually got — so verifying
#     the API is really being hit never involves guessing.
#
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT
#   cd backend && python run.py          # serves on :8001
#   cp frontend/.env.local.example frontend/.env.local
#   cd frontend && npm run dev           # serves on :5173
#
# The port here MUST match backend/run.py. It listens on 8001, not uvicorn's
# default 8000 — point at the wrong one and the frontend silently falls back to
# the static snapshot and reports the backend as unreachable.
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8001

# DEPLOYED (set this in the Vercel dashboard, not here)
#   Point it at your Render backend to make the deployed link runnable:
#     VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://storefront-backend.onrender.com
#
#   This is SAFE to set in production. The free tier sleeps and takes ~50s to
#   wake, but the frontend never waits on it: the snapshot renders immediately
#   and live data swaps in behind it if and when the server answers. A sleeping
#   backend degrades to exactly the static experience — never a blank page.
#
#   Remember to also set CORS_EXTRA_ORIGINS on the backend to this site's origin,
#   or the browser will block every call.
